cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of unsupervised transfer of object recognition models from synthetic to real data, which is a core problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the evaluation of multiple state-of-the-art methods, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new benchmark for synthetic to real visual domain adaptation, which could also place it in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of 3D object models and object detection tasks suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
